comment:
* Social status update columns.
     *
     * @see StatusUpdates
     * @see ContactsContract.Data

variables.name: PRESENCE
variables.comment:
* Contact's latest presence level. *

Type: INTEGER (one of the values below)

variables.name: STATUS_TIMESTAMP
variables.comment:
* The absolute time in milliseconds when the latest status was inserted/updated. *

Type: NUMBER

variables.name: STATUS_RES_PACKAGE
variables.comment:
* The package containing resources for this status: label and icon. *

Type: TEXT

variables.name: STATUS_LABEL
variables.comment:
* The resource ID of the label describing the source of the status update, e.g. "Google * Talk". This resource should be scoped by the {@link #STATUS_RES_PACKAGE}. *

Type: NUMBER

variables.name: STATUS_ICON
variables.comment:
* The resource ID of the icon for the source of the status update. * This resource should be scoped by the {@link #STATUS_RES_PACKAGE}. *

Type: NUMBER

variables.name: CHAT_CAPABILITY
variables.comment:
* Contact's audio/video chat capability level. *

Type: INTEGER (one of the values below)

variables.name: CAPABILITY_HAS_VOICE
variables.comment:
* An allowed flag of {@link #CHAT_CAPABILITY}. Indicates audio-chat capability (microphone
         * and speaker)

variables.name: CAPABILITY_HAS_VIDEO
variables.comment:
* An allowed flag of {@link #CHAT_CAPABILITY}. Indicates that the contact's device can
         * display a video feed.

variables.name: CAPABILITY_HAS_CAMERA
variables.comment:
* An allowed flag of {@link #CHAT_CAPABILITY}. Indicates that the contact's device has a
         * camera that can be used for video chat (e.g. a front-facing camera on a phone).
